<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="annoyed-adj">annoyed <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ə'nɔɪd/    美 /ə'nɔɪd/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>恼怒的；烦恼的：</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>(be) annoyed at / with sb:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She was annoyed with Duncan for forgetting to phone.
邓肯忘了打电话让她很生气。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) annoyed about / by sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Are you annoyed by the quality of your sleep?
你在为睡眠质量不高而烦恼吗？</p><footer>2008 湖南</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) annoyed + that 从句：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Mr Davies was annoyed that the books were missing.
那些图书不见了，戴维斯先生很生气。</p></div></div>